Q. Given a binary number, convert the number to decimal format.

Find the length of the binary number, run a loop from the end of the string to
the first element and start multiplying the number (if 1) from the powers of 2^0 
for each index moving onwards and skip multiplication for powers of 0 while 
incrementing power of 2.


int convertToDecimal (string x){
  int len= x.length;
  int p2=1, ans=0;

  for(i= len-1 to 0){
    if(x[i] == '1') num= num+ p2;
    p2= p2*2;
  }
  return ans;
}

